      <article class="lead">
        <h2>The US declined to renew USMCA in its current form</h2>
        <p>The agreement remains in force, but it now enters annual reviews through 2036. That leaves the rules behind roughly <b>$1.8 trillion in North American trade</b> open to negotiation every year.</p>
        <div class="src"><span>Trade</span><span>Jul 1</span><a href="https://ustr.gov/about/policy-offices/press-office/press-releases/2026/july/ambassador-greer-issues-statement-usmca-joint-review">USTR · Original statement ↗</a></div>
      </article>
      <article class="story">
        <div class="story-tag">Economy &amp; money</div>
        <div><h3>Inflation fell to 3.37%, back inside Banxico’s target band</h3><p>It is the third consecutive monthly decline. Core inflation remains higher, so the underlying pressure has not disappeared.</p><div class="src"><span>Jun 2026</span><a href="https://www.banxico.org.mx/AplBusquedasBM2/bsiewww.jsp?_page=1&amp;_action=search&amp;_lang=es&amp;_userquery=SP1">INEGI / Banxico · Open series ↗</a></div></div>
      </article>
      <article class="story">
        <div class="story-tag">Politics</div>
        <div><h3>The second judicial reform is now official</h3><p>Pending judicial elections move to 2028 and the Supreme Court’s structure changes again. Secondary laws are still moving through Congress.</p><div class="src"><span>Jun 2</span><a href="https://www.dof.gob.mx/">Diario Oficial · Read decree ↗</a></div></div>
      </article>
      <article class="story">
        <div class="story-tag">Economy &amp; money</div>
        <div><h3>Moody’s cuts Mexico to Baa3, the last investment-grade rung</h3><p>The main concerns are the cost of supporting Pemex and persistent fiscal deficits. S&amp;P’s outlook is also negative.</p><div class="src"><span>May 20</span><a href="https://www.gob.mx/hacienda">Hacienda / Moody’s · Open source ↗</a></div></div>
      </article>
    </section>

