  <section class="topics" aria-labelledby="topics-title">
    <div class="topics-h"><div class="mod-k">This week</div><div class="topics-asof">Updated Jul 13</div></div>
    <h2 class="topics-title" id="topics-title">Mexico by topic</h2>
    <div class="topics-grid">
      <article class="topic"><a class="topic-head" href="/topics-start-mockup.html?t=economy"><span class="topic-k">Economy &amp; money</span><span class="topic-go">More →</span></a><p class="topic-summary">Inflation is back inside Banxico’s band and activity is growing again, but core inflation and interest rates remain higher.</p><a class="topic-link" href="/chart.html?v=banxico-inflacion,banxico-inflacion-subyacente"><span class="topic-story">June inflation fell to 3.37%; core is 4.03%</span><span class="topic-meta">INEGI / Banxico · Jun 2026</span></a><a class="topic-link" href="/chart.html?v=banxico-igae"><span class="topic-story">April activity was 2.17% above a year earlier</span><span class="topic-meta">INEGI / Banxico · Apr 2026</span></a></article>
      <article class="topic"><a class="topic-head" href="/topics-start-mockup.html?t=payments"><span class="topic-k">Payments</span><span class="topic-go">More →</span></a><p class="topic-summary">Digital rails and card payments are growing. Cash still handles most small purchases, and account access remains the limit.</p><a class="topic-link" href="/chart.html?v=banxico-spei-operaciones"><span class="topic-story">SPEI processed 811 million transfers in June</span><span class="topic-meta">Banxico · Jun 2026</span></a><a class="topic-link" href="https://www.inegi.org.mx/programas/enif/2024/"><span class="topic-story">85.2% still use cash most often for small purchases</span><span class="topic-meta">INEGI · ENIF 2024</span></a></article>
      <article class="topic"><a class="topic-head" href="/topics-start-mockup.html?t=trade"><span class="topic-k">Trade</span><span class="topic-go">More →</span></a><p class="topic-summary">Exports and imports are both near record highs. Four-fifths of Mexican goods exports go to the United States.</p><a class="topic-link" href="/chart.html?v=banxico-exports-total,banxico-imports-total"><span class="topic-story">Exports reached $723bn over the latest 12 months</span><span class="topic-meta">Banxico · 12m to May 2026</span></a><a class="topic-link" href="/topics-start-mockup.html?t=trade#topicModules"><span class="topic-story">The US bought 81.24% of Mexico’s 2024 exports</span><span class="topic-meta">UN COMTRADE · 2024</span></a></article>
      <article class="topic"><a class="topic-head" href="/topics-start-mockup.html?t=politics"><span class="topic-k">Politics</span><span class="topic-go">More →</span></a><p class="topic-summary">The governing coalition has a lower-house supermajority. Coalition leaders reported 86 of 128 senators in Nov 2025; the Senate margin is tighter.</p><a class="topic-link" href="https://sitl.diputados.gob.mx/LXVI_leg/info_diputados.php"><span class="topic-story">The governing bloc holds 364 of 500 deputies</span><span class="topic-meta">Cámara de Diputados · Mar 2026 roster</span></a><a class="topic-link" href="https://www.as-coa.org/articles/approval-tracker-mexicos-president-claudia-sheinbaum"><span class="topic-story">Approval ranges from 49% to 68% by pollster</span><span class="topic-meta">AS/COA tracker · Jun 2026</span></a></article>
      <article class="topic"><a class="topic-head" href="/topics-start-mockup.html?t=society"><span class="topic-k">Society &amp; security</span><span class="topic-go">More →</span></a><p class="topic-summary">Poverty and real minimum wages improved. Informality still covers more than half of workers; the homicide rate rose in 2024 but remains below 2018.</p><a class="topic-link" href="https://www.inegi.org.mx/contenidos/saladeprensa/boletines/2025/pm/pm2025_08.pdf"><span class="topic-story">Poverty fell to 29.6% in 2024</span><span class="topic-meta">INEGI · 2024</span></a><a class="topic-link" href="https://www.inegi.org.mx/contenidos/saladeprensa/boletines/2025/edr/EDR2024-def_RR.pdf"><span class="topic-story">The homicide rate was 25.8 per 100,000</span><span class="topic-meta">INEGI · 2024 definitive</span></a></article>
      <article class="topic"><a class="topic-head" href="/topics-start-mockup.html?t=usmexico"><span class="topic-k">U.S.–Mexico</span><span class="topic-go">More →</span></a><p class="topic-summary">USMCA remains in force, but the unresolved review brings the trade rules back to the table every year.</p><a class="topic-link" href="https://ustr.gov/about/policy-offices/press-office/press-releases/2026/july/ambassador-greer-issues-statement-usmca-joint-review"><span class="topic-story">The US declined to renew USMCA in its current form</span><span class="topic-meta">USTR · Jul 1</span></a><a class="topic-link" href="https://www.census.gov/foreign-trade/balance/c2010.html"><span class="topic-story">Two-way goods trade reached $87.2bn in May</span><span class="topic-meta">U.S. Census · May 2026</span></a></article>
